Meta Shops require TWO components:

================================================================================
PART 1: FEED EXPORT - Customize URLs to Meta Format (?products=ID)
================================================================================

Hook: wt_feed_facebook_product_checkout_link
File: Add to your theme's functions.php or custom plugin

<?php
/**
 * Part 1: Customize feed URLs for Meta Shops format.
 * This makes the feed export Meta-compatible URLs.
 */
add_filter(
    'wt_feed_facebook_product_checkout_link',
    function( $checkout_url, $product ) {
        $product_id = $product->get_id();
        if ( ! $product_id ) {
            return $checkout_url;
        }
        $checkout_base = trailingslashit( wc_get_checkout_url() );
        $meta_checkout_url = $checkout_base . '?products=' . intval( $product_id );
        return esc_url( $meta_checkout_url );
    },
    10,
    2
);
?>

RESULT: Feed now exports URLs like: https://example.com/checkout/?products=123

================================================================================
PART 2: FRONTEND - Handle ?products= Parameter in WooCommerce
================================================================================

Hook: template_redirect (WordPress core hook)
File: Add to your theme's functions.php or custom plugin

This handles incoming requests with ?products= parameter and adds items to cart.

<?php
/**
 * Part 2: Handle Meta Shops checkout URLs on the frontend.
 * Detects ?products= parameter, adds items to cart, redirects to checkout.
 */
add_action( 'template_redirect', function() {
    // Check if products parameter exists
    if ( ! isset( $_GET['products'] ) ) {
        return;
    }

    // Get product IDs from URL parameter
    $product_ids = sanitize_text_field( $_GET['products'] );

    if ( empty( $product_ids ) ) {
        return;
    }

    // Parse multiple products if comma-separated
    $product_array = array_filter( array_map( 'intval', explode( ',', $product_ids ) ) );

    if ( empty( $product_array ) ) {
        return;
    }

    // Add products to cart
    foreach ( $product_array as $product_id ) {
        // Verify product exists
        if ( wc_get_product( $product_id ) ) {
            WC()->cart->add_to_cart( $product_id, 1 );
        }
    }

    // Redirect to checkout
    wp_safe_remote_post( wc_get_checkout_url() );
    wp_redirect( wc_get_checkout_url() );
    exit;
}, 20 );
?>

WHAT THIS DOES:
1. Detects incoming request with ?products=123 (or ?products=123,456)
2. Parses the product IDs from the URL
3. Adds each product to WooCommerce cart
4. Redirects user to checkout page
5. User completes purchase in standard WooCommerce checkout

================================================================================
COMPLETE FLOW:
================================================================================

1. Meta Shops displays product with checkout URL: 
   https://example.com/checkout/?products=123

2. User clicks "Check Out"

3. Request arrives at your WooCommerce site with ?products=123

4. PART 2 code detects this parameter, adds product 123 to cart

5. User is redirected to: https://example.com/checkout/

6. Standard WooCommerce checkout is displayed

7. User completes payment using your normal payment gateway

================================================================================
NOTES:
================================================================================

- PART 1 is handled by WebToffee Product Feed plugin (wt_feed_facebook_product_checkout_link)
- PART 2 is standard WooCommerce code (template_redirect hook) that YOU add to your site
- PART 2 code should be added to functions.php or a custom must-use plugin
- For multiple channels: Modify Part 1 hook name (facebook → google, twitter, etc.)
- Part 2 works for all channels that export ?products= format
- Both parts are required for complete Meta Shops integration
- Test thoroughly before going live

FOR MULTIPLE PRODUCTS:
- Feed can export: ?products=123,456,789
- Part 2 code handles parsing and adding all products
- Users can checkout multiple products at once
